Complete Class Implementation Summary
Core Service Layer (15 classes)

CardMailerServiceImpl.java - Main orchestrator (0000-MAINLINE-CONTROL)
DatabaseAccessService.java - DB access (1100-ACCESS-DB2-TABLES)
MessageProcessingService.java - Message processing (1120, 1121, 1150)
AddressFormattingService.java - Address formatting (1110, 2010, 5000)
CurrencyFormattingService.java - Currency handling
InventoryUpdateService.java - Inventory updates (4000)

Processor Layer (4 classes)

MessageTextProcessor.java - (1130-EVAL-MSG-TEXT)
TextIdEvaluator.java - (1135-EVAL-TEXT-ID-NUM)
MessageSequenceProcessor.java - (1140)
AreaMessageProcessor.java - Area message logic

Formatter Layer (5 classes)

AddressFormatter.java - (1110, 2010 paragraphs)
PhoneNumberFormatter.java - Phone formatting
CreditLimitFormatter.java - (1136-FORMAT-CREDIT)
ZipCodeFormatter.java - ZIP/postal code
TextJustifier.java - (1137-LEFT-JUSTIFY)

Repository Layer (10 classes)

CardMailerRepository.java - (1200, 8100, 8500)
CustomerRepository.java - (8000)
MailerMessageRepository.java - (8300, 8310, 8320)
AccountRepository.java - Account queries
InventoryRepository.java - (4000)
CountryRepository.java - (5000)
AddressRepository.java - Address queries
ClientRepository.java - Client queries
FormRepository.java - Forms queries
RecordRepository.java - Record queries

Entity Layer (10 classes)
26-35. JPA entities for all database tables
Model Layer (8 classes)

WorkArea.java - All WS- variables
CommonFields.java - CMS-COMMON-FIELDS
CardMailerInfo.java - CARD-MAILER-INFORMATION
AreaMessage.java - Area message structure
PhoneNumber.java - Phone structure
41-43. Various segment models

DTO Layer (3 classes)

CardMailerRequest.java - Request DTO
CardMailerResponse.java - Response DTO
ErrorResponse.java - Error response

Enum Layer (6 classes)

CurrencyCode.java - Currency codes
CountryCode.java - Country codes
AccountType.java - Account types
MessageType.java - Message types
TextIdType.java - Text ID types
SqlState.java - SQL states

Exception Layer (4 classes)

CardMailerException.java - Base exception
InvalidDataException.java - Data validation
DataAccessException.java - Database errors
GlobalExceptionHandler.java - (9100-ERROR-ROUTINE)

Utility Layer (4 classes)

DateUtil.java - Date operations
StringUtil.java - String operations
CurrencyUtil.java - Currency utilities
FormatUtil.java - General formatting
Service Package Bloat - 44 service classes is excessive. Many of these could be consolidated:

PARA_1137_CreditAmountFormattingService.java
PARA_1137_CreditLimitFormattingService.java
PARA_1137_CurrencyFormattingService.java

These three should be ONE CreditFormattingService.java
COBOL File in Service Package - CCPBS610.cobol should NOT be in your Java service package. This is a critical organizational error.
Missing Packages from Claude's Design:

No formatter package - All formatting logic is mixed into services
No processor package - Message processing logic is scattered
No validator package - Data validation not separated
No enums package - No type-safe enumerations for codes
No exception package - Error handling not organized
No util package - Utility methods likely duplicated across services
No dto package - Request/Response objects missing


Over-Engineering with PARA_ Prefix - While traceability is good, having PARA_1110_AddressFormattingService.java is too literal. Better name: AddressFormattingService.java with JavaDoc referencing PARA_1110
Duplicate/Similar Services:

CardMailerInitializationService.java AND PARA_1000_CardMailerInitializationService.java - Redundant?
InventoryUpdateProcessingService.java AND Entry_para_InventoryUpdateProcessingService.java - Why both?




Recommended Consolidation Strategy
Consolidate These Services:
Group 1: Formatting (10 → 3 classes)
PARA_1136_CreditLimitFormattingService.java
PARA_1137_CreditAmountFormattingService.java     → CreditFormattingService.java
PARA_1137_CurrencyFormattingService.java

PARA_1110_AddressFormattingService.java
PARA_2000_MailerAddressFormattingService.java    → AddressFormattingService.java
PARA_2010_MailingAddressFormattingService.java

PARA_1145_PostalCodeFormattingService.java       → (Keep separate)
Group 2: Message Processing (7 → 2 classes)
PARA_1120_AreaMessageProcessingService.java
PARA_1130_MessageTemplateProcessingService.java
PARA_1135_VariableTextReplacementService.java   → MessageProcessingService.java
PARA_1140_MessagePlacementService.java

PARA_1121_MessageInformationRetrievalService.java
PARA_1150_MessageDisplayAreaService.java        → MessageRetrievalService.java
PARA_1500_MessageSuppressionService.java
Group 3: Database Operations (9 → 3 classes)
PARA_8000_ClientAddressRetrievalService.java
PARA_8100_CardMailingOptionsService.java
PARA_8200_EnvelopeFormSelectionService.java     → DatabaseAccessService.java
PARA_8310_MailerMessageRetrievalService.java
PARA_8400_FormInformationRetrievalService.java

PARA_8500_CardMailerIdentificationService.java
PARA_8600_AnnualFeeDateRetrievalService.java    → DataRetrievalService.java
PARA_8700_DirectDepositAccountRetrievalService.java

PARA_8320_MessageCursorClosureService.java      → (Merge into MessageRetrievalService)
